charges.charge_disposition: Defendant is committed to the custody of the Bureau of Prisons for 31 months. This term consists of 27 months on Count 1 of the Indictment with credit given for 20 months already in custody and 24 months on Count 3, to be served consecutively. Supervised Release for a term of three years. This term consists of three years on Count 1 and one year on Count 3 of the Indictment, all such terms to run concurrently, under the terms and conditions of the U.S. Probation Office and General Order 05-02, and General Order 01-05. Special assessment of $200. Restitution of $85.74. All fines waived.
